				<wikidot:authorName>ecdysis</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3739601</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I had trouble understanding it the first read through. Normally I reread articles I don't understand the first time, as the second or third reading usually sheds some light. But the format screw requires the reader to clear browser cache even reread the article. I think it would improve it to make it loop. The last page already breaks the 4th wall anyway because it's no longer in-character (and while seeing the deletion page was cool for a second, ultimately this broke the immersion for me - but maybe it's just me.)</p> <p>The format screw is a cool idea and implemented well. But it felt like this gimmick itself was the most interesting part of the article. The SCP itself wasn't really described, the story felt vague, so it made little impression on me. -1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
