					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381322#post-3725755</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-5381322/scp-3340#post-3725755</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 01 Mar 2018 17:51:31 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Kid F</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2782678</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I applaud the gimmick, but it does a disservice to the article. It basically serves as a substitute for an interesting narrative, and considering the small avalanche of meta format screws that have recently been posted to the site, I've had my fill. You took an interesting concept but failed to develop it very far, making the gimmick feel like a cop-out way of eliciting a reaction from the reader. Sure, its cool, but it just left me thinking of the ways in which you could have explored the concept instead of keeping it as shallow as it is now.</p> <p>I don't know if its just because meta is in right now, but I think it points to the fact that because all the low-hanging fruit (from a conceptual perspective) has already been plucked, gimmicks have become the newest fashion in SCP articles. I'm a bit disheartened by this, but I understand and appreciate that, given all the easy stuff has already been written, it's just becoming harder and harder to come up with unique, interesting concepts anymore.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
